  "body": " Deferred Annuities  The word \"deferred\" refers to something that is put-off. For example, a retirement package is sometimes called \"deferred compensation.\" A deferred annuity is an annuity whose payments do not begin for some time in the future. The present value of a deferred annuity is denoted .    Let's start with an example. Suppose we have an annuity that pays 155 at the end of every year for 12 years with an effective annual interest rate of . The first payment is 9 years from today.    Generate a timeline, carefully indicating where and value the annuity (note that you will have to figure out what is!).    Calculate the present value of the deferred annuity.    How did you perform the calculation -- using or ? Why? What are the advantages and disadvantages of your choice?    Write down a formula for .    ðŸ§® Calculator Tip You can calculate the present values of deferred annuities in the financial calculator by first calculating the present value (or, if you prefer, ). Then, press the FV button, change the PMT to 0, and set N to .  Try this with the value we just calculated. Do you prefer the financial calculator or not? Why?      Calculate the present values of the following deferred annuities.                     For the deferred annuities in describe a transaction described by that notation.      You are given that . Find .      What, if anything, do you think you need to memorize from this activity? How can you minimize what needs to be memorized?    "
