  "body": "  Several other factors impact interest rates on corporate bonds. Describe the impact of each of the following:     Rating . Independent agencies (such as Moody's or S&P) rate the creditworthiness of corporate bonds. The highest is AAA.     Seniority . In the event a corporation is liquidated in bankruptcy, some bondholders have a higher claim to the proceeds of the sale. The debt senior bondholders hold is paid off first, whatever is left is available for junior ( subordinated ) bondholders and other debtholders.     Call\/Put Options . As we saw in , some bonds involve call provisions allowing issuers to retire the bond early. Some bonds have put provisions which allow the bondholder to sell the bond back to the issuer.   "
